  "target_response": {
    "text": "HRV is the variation in timing between your heartbeats, measured overnight. Counterintuitively, more variation is the good direction — it usually means your nervous system is in rest-and-recover mode rather than fight-or-flight. The number only means something against your own history, not anyone else's, and against yours today is a shade soft: 61 ms versus a 30-day average of 68.1 and a weekly average of 69. A single morning below baseline is normal noise; several in a row is what would actually matter. Worth noting your reading comes through a health platform that calculates HRV differently from some devices, one more reason to ignore other people's numbers. Check where tomorrow lands before reading anything into today's dip.",
